arxiv_id : 1711.07540
title    : Post-prior equivalence for transfer reactions with complex potentials
authors  : Lei, Jin; Moro, Antonio M.
date     : 2017-11-20    doi: 10.1103/PhysRevC.97.011601
cats     : Nuclear Theory
tex_dir  : /Volumes/KINGSTON/nucl-th_tex_files/1711.07540
abstract : In this paper, we address the problem of the post-prior equivalence in the calculation of inclusive breakup and transfer cross sections. For that, we employ the model proposed by Ichimura, Austern, and Vincent [Phys. Rev. C 32, 431 (1985)], conveniently generalized to include the part of the cross section corresponding the transfer to bound states. We pay particular attention to the case in which the unobserved particle is left in a bound state of the residual nucleus, in which case the theory prescribes the use of a complex potential, responsible for the spreading width of the populated single-particle states. We see that the introduction of this complex potential gives rise to an additional term in the prior cross section formula, not present in the usual case of real binding potentials. The equivalence is numerically tested for reaction induced by deuterons.
